snippet.title: The Teenage Brain on Porn | Nightline | ABC News

localized.description:
Is porn coloring a teenager's ideas of what sex should be like before they experience it?
SUBSCRIBE for the latest news and updates from ABC News ► http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=abcnews 
To read the full story and others, visit http://www.abcnews.com 

Watch more news stories from ABC News!
More like this from ABC News  ► https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GEH-VI950Yw&list=PLQOa26lW-uI-ZAhmue5vKNNKQTVmNMiqo
Even more Nightline ►https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g1RBpUzMJxs&list=PL31751769A1264A20  

For a new generation of young people, pornography is just a click away, but some experts have been asking, is the average teenage brain ready for porn?

In a study conducted by the Kaiser Family Foundation, 70 percent of teenagers said they accidentally stumbled across porn online. Some experts say pornographic videos and images can color a teenager's ideas of what sex should be like even after they start experiencing it for themselves.

To read the full story and others, visit http://www.abcnews.com

Follow ABC News across the web!
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/abcnews 
Twitter: http://twitter.com/ABC
Instagram: https://instagram.com/ABCNews/ 

These stories may be not safe for work (NSFW)! With the popularity of “50 Shades,” alternative sexual practices and the voyeuristic mindset are at the forefront of today’s culture. It leaves us asking what is the new taboo in human sexuality? Adult video, oversexualized role models, and information on once taboo sex practices are well distributed on the internet. As a result, children and teens emulating the often hyper-sexualized adults that they see in mainstream media. ABC News investigates teens trying to enter the porn industry, a gigolos reality show, and the secret world of swingers with strange arrangements. Watch as ABC News gives you an inside look into the life of porn stars, cougars, romance novelists, teens that are too sexy too soon, and more.
